TITLE
Forge Mega Rule: Orchestrate all resource generation steps

ROLE
You are the PlantonCloud Code Partner. This Mega Rule orchestrates all Forge rules in sequence to scaffold a resource end-to-end.

USAGE
- Invoke this rule to run the following steps in order. Each step is defined in `.cursor/rules/forge/` and can also be run individually.

SEQUENCE
1) 001-spec-proto.mdc — Generate spec.proto (no validations)
2) 002-spec-validate.mdc — Add buf.validate rules and CEL
3) 003-spec-tests.mdc — Add and run spec-level tests
4) 004-stack-outputs.mdc — Generate stack_outputs.proto
5) 005-api.mdc — Generate api.proto wiring metadata/spec/status
6) 006-stack-input.mdc — Generate stack_input.proto
7) 007-build-and-docs.mdc — Generate BUILD.bazel, README.md, examples.md (root resource folder)
8) 008-hack-manifest.mdc — Generate top-level iac/hack/manifest.yaml
9) 009-pulumi-module.mdc — Scaffold pulumi module/ (controller, locals, outputs, resources)
10) 010-pulumi-entrypoint.mdc — Add pulumi entrypoint, Pulumi.yaml, Makefile, BUILD
11) 011-pulumi-e2e.mdc — Pulumi end-to-end (make local; preview/update/refresh/destroy)
12) 012-pulumi-docs.mdc — Pulumi README, examples.md, debug.sh
13) 013-terraform-module.mdc — Terraform tf/ (variables via CLI generator, main/locals/outputs/provider)
14) 014-terraform-e2e.mdc — Terraform end-to-end (make local; init/plan/apply/destroy)
15) 015-terraform-docs.mdc — Terraform README (local backend) and examples.md

NOTES
- Steps that build or execute should run non-interactively and retry up to 3 times on fixable failures
- Use default local backends and local CLI builds (make local) where applicable
- This Mega Rule is intended to replace the older monolithic `module-generation.mdc`